‘Being John Malkovich’

Starts streaming: Feb. 1

Feb. 1 Save To Watch Ribbon Save to Watch Like Heart Shape Like

The screenwriter Charlie Kaufman burst onto the scene with this wholly original, playfully surreal comedy about a portal into John Malkovich’s head that allows people to experience his state of being for 15 minutes at a time. Kaufman and director Spike Jonze delight in playing around in this metaphysical space, while also offering up such absurd creations as an office space on a half-floor and a 60-foot Emily Dickinson puppet. Yet “Being John Malkovich” is sneakily moving, turning on the common and melancholy yearning of what it’s like to want to escape your own skin.

