‘Blue Crush’

Starts streaming: Feb. 1

Save To Watch Ribbon Save to Watch Like Heart Shape Like

Loosely based on Susan Orlean’s magazine article “Surf Girls of Maui,” this late-summer hit from 2002 may be primarily about beautiful beaches and bodies in motion, but it overachieves in every respect. Director John Stockwell, who made the fine teen romance “Crazy/Beautiful,” has a good handle on the emotional state of a gifted young surfer (Kate Bosworth) who’s trying to make it back in the water after near-fatal incident. Her comeback follows the usual sports-movie formula, but for surfing footage so spectacularly rendered, that much is forgiven.

