‘Friday Night Lights’

Starts streaming: Feb. 1

Save To Watch Ribbon Save to Watch Like Heart Shape Like

Before “Friday Night Lights” was developed into one of best dramas in recent network history, it existed onscreen as a solid adaptation of Buzz Bissinger’s nonfiction book about a football-obsessed small town in Texas. Director Peter Berg doesn’t have time to explore fully the characters and social complexities of Bissinger’s book, but he does capture the pressure-cooker atmosphere of a place where football is religion. All that pressure is brought to bear on the coach (Billy Bob Thornton), who’s expected to win every game or lose his job.

