‘Moon’

Starts streaming: Feb. 1

Feb. 1 Save To Watch Ribbon Save to Watch Like Heart Shape Like

Duncan Jones’s auspicious directorial debut feels composed of equal parts “2001: A Space Odyssey” and “Dark Star.” Like the “2001,” it’s a metaphysical head-trip about an astronaut (Sam Rockwell) relying on a possibly diabolical sentient computer (GERTY, voiced by Kevin Spacey) for companionship. Like “Dark Star,” it has an abundance of low-budget charm, with a space station set that looks like an old rental, and an openness to whimsy. Rockwell stars as a loopy energy contractor who’s thrown into chaos just as his final year on a lunar outpost is about to end.

