‘Seeing Allred’

Starts streaming: Feb. 9

Save To Watch Ribbon Save to Watch Like Heart Shape Like

The nation’s most prominent and controversial feminist lawyer, Gloria Allred was in the news recently for representing one of the women accusing Roy Moore, the Alabama Republican candidate for United States Senate, of sexual misconduct with a minor. This admiring documentary profile from Sophie Sartain and Roberta Grossman catches Allred just as she was shining a big media spotlight on a wave of Bill Cosby’s accusers. But the film also takes a broader view of Allred’s advocacy for women, and how it was able to develop considerable power.

